observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our recommendations that:

The Municipal Mayor direct the Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical count of all PPE covering all offices at least once a year, submit the RPCPPE, in its prescribed form, that includes all properties and the Report on Unserviceable Properties and coordinate closely with the Municipal Accountant for the reconciliation of the RPCPPE with the accounting records;

The Municipal Accountant maintain PPELCs for all PPEs;




The General Services Officer – Designate create PCs per category of PPE indicating therein the relevant information for proper monitoring; and 

The Municipality undertake the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances of government agencies as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020.

We recommended the following:

The Municipal Mayor reconstitute a new Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical count of inventories semestrally, submit the RPCI and coordinate closely with the Municipal Accountant for the effective and efficient monitoring of inventories;

The Municipal Mayor assign additional personnel to assist the General Services Officer – Designate in the performance of her functions;

The Municipal Mayor set up a stockroom where inventories will be delivered and stored prior to issuance to end-users;

The Municipal Accountant apply consistently the perpetual inventory method in accounting for supplies and materials inventories;

The Municipal Accountant use the SSMI as basis for drawing the JEV to recognize the issuances or the corresponding supplies and materials expenses;

The Municipal Accountant maintain SLCs for all types of inventories;

The General Services Officer – Designate summarize the RIS, prepare the SSMI and submit to the Municipal Accountant to serve as basis in accounting for the issuances of supplies and materials; and

The General Services Officer – Designate maintain SC for all types of inventories.

We reiterated our previous recommendation that:

The Local Chief Executive create a Disposal Committee who will evaluate and appraise the value of the properties to be disposed;

The Disposal Committee prepare an Inventory and Inspection Report on Unserviceable Properties (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report (WMR);

The Municipal Mayor request inspection and valuation of the aforementioned properties to the COA Technical Audit Specialists (TAS);

Based on the COA TAS recommendations, the agency undertake the disposal of properties; and

The Municipal Accountant draw a JEV to drop the unserviceable properties from the books of accounts.

