We reiterated our previous recommendations that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) require the Inventory Committee to:

Conduct annual inventory taking for PPE;


Prepare a Report on Physical Count of PPE with complete data;


Instruct the General Services Office (GSO) and the Municipal Accountant to maintain property ledger cards and subsidiary ledger for PPE respectively, and ensure that records are reconciled; and

Properties which were not yet completed/turned over to the Municipality should not be included in the RPCPPE but should be treated as Construction-in-Progress.

We recommended the following:

The Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Assessor to prepare and submit a schedule bearing the names of landowners with areas and assessed value of the lands they own to the Municipal Treasurer to serve as basis for updating of the Real Property Tax Account Register/Taxpayers’ Index Cards;

The Municipal Treasurer update his Real Property Tax Account Register/Taxpayers’ Index Cards and submit a certified list of taxpayers with the corresponding amounts to the Municipal Accountant at the beginning of the calendar year.  The total amount in the certified list should be reconciled with the total amount per schedule furnished by the Municipal Assessor;

The Municipal Accountant prepare a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to set up the receivable account based on the duly certified list and ensure the proper recording of collection in the corresponding subsidiary ledger; and

The Municipal Accountant analyze the causes of these discrepancies between reciprocal accounts and draw the necessary journal entry vouchers to adjust their balances.

We recommended the following:

The LGU appropriate funds for the titling of the lots purchased;

The Municipal Assessor’s Office follow-up the titling of all parcels of land of the Municipal Government;


The Municipal Accounting Office and the Treasurer’s Office maintain complete records of real properties owned by the Municipality; and

The Municipal Accountant should review the basis of recording of the amount in the books of accounts and ensure that it was based on cost.

